"""Shared contracts and utilities for the {{ project_slug }} experiments.

Batches travel as ``tensordict.TensorDictBase``. `Model` maps a batch of named
tensors to a batch of named tensors; `Loss` is a metric whose ``update_and_loss``
also returns the `Scalar` ready for ``.backward()``. `Data` builds the train
dataloader and named eval dataloaders from datasets, with its loader options in
`LoaderKwargs`; `TensorDictDataset` serves a batched TensorDict as a map-style
dataset. `EvalSchedule` says when one eval split's metrics are computed and
`ScheduleTracker` makes the per-step firing decisions. `CheckpointState` is the
training snapshot a checkpoint callback hands to a logger. `seed_parameters`
re-initializes a module's parameters from an explicit generator.

The concrete implementations live in four subpackages: `core.train` (the
training loop `fit`, its `evaluate` pass, the `EvalSplit` bundle, and the
`TrainContext` threaded through both), `core.metrics` (the `Metric` contract and
the shipped metrics), `core.callbacks` (the `Callback` interface and the shipped
callbacks), and `core.logger` (the logging backends).
"""

